sql:
SELECT wsm.metadata, wsm.sensor_accuracy, wsm.sensor_calibration_date
FROM weather_station_metadata wsm
WHERE wsm.station_id = 0;

SELECT AVG(sensor_accuracy) AS average_accuracy
FROM weather_station_metadata
WHERE metadata_source = 'manual';

SELECT * 
FROM weather_station_status 
WHERE status = 'online' OR status = 'offline';

external_knowledge:
Active weather stations refer to those that are currently operational and reporting data; 
A weather station's location is its geographical position;
Observation source refers to the method or device used to collect weather data, such as sensors or manual readings;
Forecast source refers to the model or system used to generate weather forecasts.

sql:
SELECT wo.temperature, wf.forecast_temperature
FROM weather_observations wo
JOIN weather_forecasts wf ON wo.station_id = wf.station_id;
